  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Invite 3–4 students to share their pictures. Display the pictures for the class.</li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Por qué todas las imágenes tienen mariquitas?</q> (We all had to draw some ladybugs.)
      </li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Por qué no todas tienen el mismo número de mariquitas?</q> (The number was different each time you rolled.)
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Descripción del desarrollo de lenguaje matemático -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="language-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>MLR8 Discussion Supports. Synthesis: Some students may benefit from the opportunity to rehearse what they will say with a partner before they share with the whole class. </p>
    <p>Advances: Speaking</p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Estrategias de acceso para estudiantes con discapacidades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="accesibility-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Action and Expression: Internalize Executive Functions. Check for understanding by inviting 1–2 students to rephrase directions in their own words. If time permits, invite students to share the “moves” they will make when it is their turn.</p>
    <p>Supports accessibility for: Memory, Organization</p>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

